Backend:
npm install socket.io

# 'io' from socket.io 
- socket instance for connection and disconnections
- io.on('connection', callback(socket)) it can show onnection each time server requested 
- the socket argument inside above arg can emit or disconnect socket based on event needed
 e.g. socket.on(eventName, callback)
 
# socket.io(eventName, callback) means receive something as connection, messages, chat messages etc. 
# socket.emit(eventName, callback) means send somthing as disconnect, messages, chat etc.

see here: https://socket.io/docs/v4/server-socket-instance/

Frontend:
npm install socket.io-client

import io from 'socket.io-client'
const socket = io();



